CORNELIUS NEPos was born about the year 100 13.c., probably at Ticinium, in Cis-Alpino Gaul. As his death did not occur until near the last quarter of the century, he lived in stirring times; yet he took no part in politics. In his life of Atticus he attempts to excuse his friend for hold- ing aloof from public affairS, and perhaps he may be considered to apologize for himself at the same time.
